ibution to markdown content itself.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"MOCK-MISS: This behavior is inherently comparative — it requires both the parse path and the trace/result recording to produce distinguishably different outputs for two classes of input. The failure mode sits at the boundary: does the system correctly route markdown-valid input to success and malformed input to a failure trace, with no overlap? A single unit cannot verify both paths and their distinct downstream records without the trace sink being real. REAL-INFRA: No subprocess or OS required; in-process wiring of parser + trace sink suffices. MOCK-HIDE: Mocking the trace sink would collapse the comparison — both paths could return mocked 'success' and the regression gate would never fire. REJECTION-GATE: System was considered but rejected — the distinguishing record can be verified with in-process module wiring; a subprocess is not needed to expose false-attribution failures.","test_description":"Wire the parser and trace sink without mocks. Run two inputs side by side: (a) valid JSON with maximally markdown-heavy string values, and (b) malformed JSON that is syntactically broken. Assert that case (a) produces zero `json_parse_failed` records and a successful result, while case (b) produces exactly one `json_parse_failed` record and no success result. This pairing directly tests the regression gate against false attribution.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.12,"Integration":0.68,"System":0.16,"Agentic":0.02,"Workflow":0.02}}]},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":3,"cache_creation_input_tokens":9949,"cache_read_input_tokens":3199,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":9949},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"321f6c0f-7330-499b-bbbf-